<div id="review_813595" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/813595" />
    <a title="Shira Karp" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6049-shira-karp"><img alt="Shira Karp" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1227748313p2/6049.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/813595?book_show_action=true">Apr 20, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Shira Karp" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Shira Karp" href="/user/show/6049-shira-karp">Shira Karp</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">People who like a lot of character development</span></div>

        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer813595" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17165821680010519815">I loved this book. It was amazing. I never thought I would get so wrapped up in a story where the main character was actually a house (or should I say a &quot;bungalow&quot; as that is how it is mostly referred to in the book). In the first few chapters it seemed obvious who the good guy and who the bad guy in the story were, but I quickly found that line blurred and throughout the whole book I didn&apos;t know who to root for, I wanted them both to win. The reason I only gave this book four stars instead of t</span>
  <span id="freeText17165821680010519815" style="display:none">I loved this book. It was amazing. I never thought I would get so wrapped up in a story where the main character was actually a house (or should I say a "bungalow" as that is how it is mostly referred to in the book). In the first few chapters it seemed obvious who the good guy and who the bad guy in the story were, but I quickly found that line blurred and throughout the whole book I didn't know who to root for, I wanted them both to win. The reason I only gave this book four stars instead of the five it should have deserved was because this book WAS amazing... until it ended. It was possibly the worst, most unsatisfying ending I've ever read. I sat there staring at the book going "That's IT? That's how he's ending the book? Did I get a copy missing the last chapter?" The ending was not worthy of the rest of the book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17165821680010519815" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


