              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6786262981815493937">The reason I love this book is because it beautifully presents a problem from two sides, then let&apos;s the reader decide which side he or she supports. This isn&apos;t foxnews. The author transitions from chapter to chapter between the two main characters, using wonderful language for each, and then lets the reader decide. Neither of the characters were perfect, but neither could be classified as &quot;bad guys&quot;. Andre Dubois III is my favorite modern author, his short stories are also amazing.</span>
