<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer15324248099816478117"><strong>Andre Dubus III</strong> is the author of <em>The Garden of Last Days</em>, <em>House of Sand and Fog</em> (a #1 <em>New York Times</em> bestseller, Oprahâ€™s Book Club pick, and finalist for the National Book Award) and <em>Townie</em>, winner of an American Academy of Arts and Letters Award in Literature. His writing has received many honors, including a Guggenheim Fellowship, a National Magazine Award, and two Pushcart Prizes. He lives with</span>
  <span id="freeText15324248099816478117" style="display:none"><strong>Andre Dubus III</strong> is the author of <em>The Garden of Last Days</em>, <em>House of Sand and Fog</em> (a #1 <em>New York Times</em> bestseller, Oprahâ€™s Book Club pick, and finalist for the National Book Award) and <em>Townie</em>, winner of an American Academy of Arts and Letters Award in Literature. His writing has received many honors, including a Guggenheim Fellowship, a National Magazine Award, and two Pushcart Prizes. He lives with his family north of Boston.</span>
